a solitary humanoid figure standing in a desolate field of dry grass, mid-torso to full-body view, frontal pose, hands raised at shoulder level in an open gesture of ambiguous invocation or surrender; figure is blindfolded with multiple layers of deep crimson thread tightly wound across the eyes, threads trailing down in irregular strands; skin pale like white porcelain or bleached bone, smooth but with faint matte microtexture, no pores or minimal pores; head shaved completely, skull shape precise and symmetrical, high realism but unnerving neutrality; lips closed, expression neutral — neither pain nor peace, only absence; figure’s proportions uncanny: not deformed, but subtly too perfect, like an artificial saint or mannequin-prophet.

(Costume & Materials)
clothing consists of layered ritualistic robes, deep crimson and burgundy tones, matte fabric with patches of dried pigment and faded stains like ceremonial residue; fabric hangs heavily, weighty drapery that suggests age, not luxury; sleeves oversized and enveloping, tapering around wrists where threads adhere; torso wrapped in a dense lattice of red threads layered in chaotic direction, like veins turned outside the body, forming organic gridded armor; necklace-like chains, amulets, bone beads, tarnished metal fragments entangled in the threads; ornaments asymmetrical, clustered more heavily on one side; all jewelry tarnished, matte, oxidized silver and bronze, no shine except rare specular highlights on edges; threads connect to environment like roots or puppet strings, trailing into grass and dissolving into mist.

(Hands & Thread Interaction)
hands coated in pigment or earth, palms and fingers stained crimson, fingertips darker as if dyed; thread strands drape from wrists and knuckles, some taut and vertical, some loose and drifting; hands held open, palms up, like someone expecting rain or offering something unseen; no gore, no wounds, no blood — dye and thread, not violence; detailed anatomy: tendons and knuckle tension visible, realistic bone structure under skin; nails short, matte, natural; subtle tremor implied by thread tension.

(Colors, Palette & Texture)
palette dominated by crimson, desaturated burgundy, muted clay red, bone white of skin, fog gray of background; environment tonality pastel-ashen; zero saturated primaries; contrast built on texture and value, not color; robes show micro-wrinkles with a mix of velvet-dust and linen-grain texture; skin matte, low specularity; porcelain feel but alive; thread texture: fibrous micro-hairs visible, frayed ends catching stray light.

(Setting & Atmosphere)
location: barren field, overgrown dry grass, horizon erased by fog; background soft, low detail, intentionally depthless, a diffuse void of pale gray mist; no buildings, no trees, no landmarks; the world feels unfinished; horizon blurred, like a memory that can’t fully load; atmosphere cold, not windy — stillness like the air before revelation; the environment gives no context — just a stage for the figure; light snowfall or drifting dust optional but subtle; feeling: ritual suspended in time.

(Lighting & Cinematography)
soft diffused daylight, overcast sky, high-key fog reducing contrast; no harsh shadows; volumetric haze around figure, slight bloom on highlights but not dreamy — clinical fog; skin illuminated with a painterly gradient, top-down falloff; edges slightly rim-lit by ambient light; camera angle straight at chest/eye height; lens 85mm or 105mm equivalent; shallow depth of field — figure sharp, environment melts; tone: photographic, not illustrative; resolution aim: 8k; clarity should reveal thread-fibers.

(Symbolism & Psychological Layer)
blindfold of thread = refusal or inability to witness truth; red = sacrifice, devotion, fate; porcelain skin = iconography of sainthood without religion; outstretched hands = negotiation with destiny; field = reality erased; threads entangling = metaphors of memory, prophecy, consequences; character feels like an oracle, or martyr of an unnamed philosophy; neither horror nor fantasy cliche — existential ritualism; resonates with imagery of:

“oracle of consequences”

“embryonic deity of unfinished myths”

“saint of unspoken contracts”

(Style & Quality Keywords)
hyperreal gothic surrealism, cinematic tableau, existential portraiture, ritualistic character design, haute-macabre, uncanny realism, art-house dark fantasy, museum photograph aesthetic, editorial fashion presentation from a parallel culture; visual lineage: Elden Ring concept art without armor, Beksiński textures without grotesque, Anselm Kiefer palette austerity, Caravaggio lighting without drama.

(Rendering Directives)
crimson threads: non-glossy, micro-fray; porcelain skin: subsurface scattering minimal; robes: linen + heavy cotton composite; mist: Gaussian gradient, not noise; no chromatic aberration, no glitch; film grain mild; clarity > softness.

(Camera & Composition)
portrait orientation; rule of thirds: head centered, hands on lower thirds; headroom moderate; robe edges nearly touching frame; negative space above implied; grass foreground slightly out of focus; camera distance: medium full-body., This workflow uses the sampler res_2s and the scheduler beta57.
